{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"3115","heading":"Youth employment policies and programs","label":"3115 Youth employment policies and programs","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s3115","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t15/ch58/schI","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft15%2Fs3115","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","References in TextFor definition of “this chapter”, referred to in subsec. (b), see References in Text note set out under .section 3102 of this title"],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":"Congressional findings","label":"a Congressional findings","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s3115/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t15/s3115","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft15%2Fs3115%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s3115/a/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t15/s3115/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft15%2Fs3115%2Fa%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"That serious unemployment and economic disadvantage of a unique nature exist among youths even under generally favorable economic conditions;1So in original. Probably should not be capitalized.1","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s3115/a/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t15/s3115/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft15%2Fs3115%2Fa%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"that this group constitutes a substantial portion of the Nation’s unemployment, and that this significantly contributes to crime, alcoholism and drug abuse, and other social and economic problems; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s3115/a/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t15/s3115/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft15%2Fs3115%2Fa%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"that many youths have special employment needs and problems which, if not promptly addressed, will substantially contribute to more severe unemployment problems in the long run.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":"Improvement and expansion","label":"b Improvement and expansion","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s3115/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t15/s3115","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft15%2Fs3115%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s3115/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t15/s3115/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft15%2Fs3115%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"include provisions designed to fully coordinate youth employment activities with other employment and training programs;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s3115/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t15/s3115/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft15%2Fs3115%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"develop a smoother transition from school to work;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s3115/b/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t15/s3115/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft15%2Fs3115%2Fb%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"prepare disadvantaged and other youths with employability handicaps for regular self-sustaining employment;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s3115/b/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t15/s3115/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft15%2Fs3115%2Fb%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"develop realistic methods for combining training with work; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"5","heading":null,"label":"5","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s3115/b/5","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t15/s3115/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft15%2Fs3115%2Fb%2F5","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"develop provisions designed to attract structurally unemployed youth into productive full-time employment through incentives to private and independent sector businesses;2So in original. The semicolon probably should be a period.2","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}
